ce:section.ce:para:
The FT-IR spectrum of GOx is quite similar to that of BSA - the appearances of bands at 1630cm−1 for the amide I, 1552cm−1 for the amide II and broadband at 3200cm−1 for the NH stretching of amino acid residues. The above-mentioned stretching frequencies are also appeared for GOx incubated in 40% ethanol. Ethanol, therefore, serves as an inducer, rather than a denaturing agent. Interestingly, the FT-IR spectrum of GOx incubated with 50μM CND in 40% ethanol is markedly different suggesting the strong interaction between amino acid chains GOx and CND. It can also be noticed that a new FTIR bands appear at 1710cm−1 (ν
                        COO−
                        ), which is the characteristics peak of CND.
